Nyam Lɛl dad eke Abraham in ew ey yony, Agar ekʼel adyↄw ab ab owʼn ew nyam ɛtŋ Sara ekʼel yↄw lewi ab ab yɛji owʼn ew nyam.<RF q=†>Abraham ew Ismaɛl Agar ab ɛtŋ lʼew Isak Sara ab. Nuŋ Ɔb 16.15; 21.2.
Adyↄw iyŋ a, wɛl ewʼr igŋ nyam lele yↄw nyam ab ecʼerur ɛm, kↄ yↄw lewi a ecʼiy a, wɛl ewʼr Nyam e low a eke ɛwar ab ɛm.<RF q=†>Nuŋ Ɔb 17.16.
Odad na ↄny akr otar ɛjeci. Ɔyↄw yony a anŋ ɛsɛ sinm yony af. Krɛkrɛ e sinm a, el Sinayi lafɛny af ecʼa, ɛtŋ li bʼew ey eke bʼel madu: ke Agar ana,
ɛtŋ Agar anake el Sinayi lafɛny a ekʼanŋ Arabi wus af a. Ɛtŋ in cɛ anake yɛfɛnyna ɛm a, nʼanŋ ɛsɛ Jerusalɛm<RF q=†>Aŋa wɛl am oc Jerusalɛm bɛbmn Jwifɛl e Nyam nuŋ igŋ ebr a, eke bʼucu ol e low ↄny es toŋ ke -lʼɛwr ɛsɛ madu af a. Ɛ̀kn 4.3 lele ow ecʼakr otar ab ab. ecʼɛb a ekʼin ecʼey ab ab el madu a.
